It reveals the overwhelming attention given to the 'auteur', as Spiegelman is often overshadowing his wife's role in editing and publishing RAW, and makes up for it by analyzing Mouly's important contributions to the history of comics. Jeet Heer makes an insightful analysis of the (creative) role of the editor, and of the power relationships structuring discourse in comics scholarship (in this case related to a kind of sexism).
