			<wp:comment_content><![CDATA[The Batman joke is a self joke.

The scene says about itself exactly as you interpreted it: try to overthink something like comics makes you sound like a pretentious jerk. And when someone tries something "the scholars" consider inferior, they dismiss the dissident; perhaps not calling the guards, but maybe with something like subtle or even aggressive scoffing.

I'm guessing McCloud himself was scoffed like this many times and, when he found himself on the position of the scholar, he simply joked about it, by exaggerating as any of old school comic makers would approve. You say comics should be fun? I found this bit pretty fun.]]></wp:comment_content>
