			<wp:comment_content><![CDATA[[&#8230;] I am not currently what you would call a &#8216;superhero comics reader&#8217;, though I did read many throughout my childhood and youth. I have spent much of my life trying to spread the word that the words &#8220;comics&#8221; and &#8220;comic books&#8221; denote a much wider cultural phenomenon than that represented by (normally USAmerican, anglophone) superheroes. However, I find myself constantly fascinated by the apparently perennial nature of the superhero &#8216;genre&#8217; (there must be a better term for that). I am also unavoidably attracted to the material fragility (and, to a large extent in my view, futility) of the &#8216;floppies&#8217;, the periodical, stapled comic books (Priego 2014a; 2014b ). [&#8230;]]]></wp:comment_content>
