		<title>#228 The Graphixia Year-End Event, 2015 Edition!</title>
		<link>http://www.graphixia.ca/2015/12/228-the-graphixia-year-end-event-2015-edition/</link>
		<pubDate>Tue, 22 Dec 2015 14:00:41 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[Grayb]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.graphixia.ca/?p=4683</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[Welcome to our annual holiday roundup. You can read previous incarnations of this post <a href="http://www.graphixia.ca/?p=4079">here (2014)</a> and <a href="http://www.graphixia.ca/?p=3377">here (2013)</a>. So here's the year that was in comics for the Graphixia Team for 2015!

<span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Best Comic Published in 2015</strong></span>

Paddy: <strong><em>Pope Hats #4</em> by Ethan Rilly.</strong> An amazing little bunch of elegant stories, told with the grace of Raymond Carver, and his first comic in full colour. It has a proper letters page, too, and his lettering is superb. Everything about it just works well.

