<a href="http://www.graphixia.ca/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/ETERNAUT-fc.jpg"><img class="wp-image-4701 size-medium alignleft" src="http://www.graphixia.ca/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/ETERNAUT-fc-300x261.jpg" alt="" width="300" height="261" /></a>Damon: <span data-sheets-value="[null,2,&quot;El Eternauta by H\u00e9ctor Germ\u00e1n Oesterheld and Francisco Solano L\u00f3pez. Argentinian political allegory as a science fiction serial from the late 1950s and finally available in an English translation. And what a wonderful package Fantagraphics have put together for the print edition.\nhttp://www.fantagraphics.com/eternaut/?desktop=\nDH&quot;]" data-sheets-userformat="[null,null,513,[null,0],null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,0]"><strong><a href="http://www.fantagraphics.com/eternaut/?desktop="><em>El Eternauta</em> by Héctor Germán Oesterheld and Francisco Solano López</a>.</strong> Argentinian political allegory as a science fiction serial from the late 1950s and finally available in an English translation. And what a wonderful package Fantagraphics have put together for the print edition.</span>

